### Register a new user (captures the returned token)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "director@brightminds.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "displayName": "Maria Director"
}

> {% client.global.set("token", response.body.token); %}

### Login (also captures the token)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "director@brightminds.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {% client.global.set("token", response.body.token); %}

### Who am I? (protected — uses the captured token)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Protected endpoint WITHOUT a token -> 401
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies

### Same endpoint WITH the token -> 200
GET http://localhost:8080/api/academies
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Wrong password -> 401
POST http://localhost:8080/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "director@brightminds.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}